  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      A 6-week in-patient and out-patient study to test the effectiveness and safety of a new
      medication in the treatment of schizophrenia
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Study will evaluate the efficacy of a new compound versus placebo in the treatment of
      patients with schizophrenia (diagnosed by DSM-IV criteria) as measured by reductions from
      baseline on the total score of the Brief Psychiatric Rating Scale (BPRS) as extracted from
      the Positive and Negative Syndrome Scale (PANSS).
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
